Wolfram Alpha is a unique computational knowledge engine developed by Wolfram Research. It's different from traditional search engines because it generates outputs by doing computations from its own internal knowledge base, rather than searching the web or a database of formatted pages.
Wolfram Alpha is particularly useful for mathematical calculations, data analysis, and generating plots and charts. It can solve equations, perform integrals, analyze statistical data, and much more. Besides mathematics, Wolfram Alpha covers a wide range of subjects including science, engineering, astronomy, economics, and geography. It can also handle queries about dates and times, weather, places, data comparison, and even linguistics.

The site also offers resources for upgrading from Python 2 to Python 3, ensuring learners and developers can stay up-to-date with the latest Python standards and practices. This accessible and comprehensive collection of Python learning tools is designed to support both self-paced study and formal instruction.

Stack Overflow is an invaluable platform for new Python programmers seeking answers to coding questions or wanting to contribute to community discussions. Its question-and-answer format allows users to ask specific Python-related queries, engage with solutions provided by experienced developers, and participate in a vibrant programming community. Beginners can also use the site to learn from existing discussions and find comprehensive answers to common coding challenges they might encounter.

Corey Schafer's YouTube channel is a treasure trove for new Python programmers, offering meticulously crafted tutorials that span from beginner to advanced levels. The content is structured to enhance a learner's programming skills progressively, with series on Python basics, web development with Django and Flask, and data analysis using Pandas. Newcomers to Python can follow along with Schafer's step-by-step guides to not only learn the language's syntax but also adopt best practices that are crucial for becoming proficient developers. His clear explanations and practical coding tips make complex topics accessible and learning an engaging experience.

Khan Academy is a well-known nonprofit educational organization that provides free online education. It aims to offer a free, world-class education for anyone, anywhere. The platform is extensive and includes instructional videos, practice exercises, and a personalized learning dashboard that empower learners to study at their own pace in and outside of the classroom.
Khan Academy covers a range of subjects beyond mathematics, including science topics such as biology, chemistry, and physics, along with humanities subjects such as history and economics, and even topics like computer programming and personal finance. The content is suitable for all ages, from early learners to college students and beyond.

New videos all the time, FunScienceDemos brings engaging demonstrations in a range of Earth/Space Science, Physical Science, Life Science, STEM Practices and Engineering topics right into your classroom or home. Marine Engineering is not as simply categorized as, for example, civil, mechanical, electrical, or chemical engineering. It is an integrated engineering effort comprising parts of many engineering disciplines directed to the development and design of systems of transport, warfare, exploration, and natural resource extraction that have only one thing in common, namely, that they operate in, or upon the surface of, a body of water. The website provides marine engineering study materials that are categorized mainly under motor engineering knowledge, general engineering knowledge, safety and environmental protection, naval architecture and ship building, marine electrical technology, and so forth and their subcategories. Launching your aerospace engineering education through edX allows you to choose from a wide variety of online coursework. Learn introductory and foundational topics in aerospace engineering, such as the basic principles behind rocket science, orbital mechanics, and best practices for astronaut safety. Other aerospace engineering courses can dive deeper into the logistics of propulsion systems, space flight, and aircraft design. Beginners can explore courses that cover fundamental engineering principles to set themselves up for success in a professional program. Industry professionals looking to accelerate their careers can explore advanced degrees or programs on more specialized topics, such as hypersonics, which focuses on studying flight speeds greater than Mach 5, or forensics engineering, which examines what goes wrong and how to prevent disasters from reoccurring.
Our website currently contains three main core subjects Flight Dynamics, Propulsion 1, and Propulsion 2. New topics will get added periodically.

openSourceLearning.resourceDescription: Did you know that the National Gallery of Art offers free learning resources and programs for audiences of all ages? To support teachers, parents and caregivers, and students, our educators created this selection of activities. Use these lesson plans, films, and other materials to explore art with kids of all ages, from preschoolers to high schoolers.

Need ideas for how to talk about art with your little ones? In each box below, you can explore artworks with your children, read books with related themes, and try your hand at making some art of your own. Download the related coloring pages and cut-outs for extra creative fun!

The Art Institute of Chicago shares its singular collections with our city and the world. We collect, care for, and interpret works of art across time, cultures, geographies, and identities, centering the vision of artists and makers. We recognize that all art is made in a particular context, demanding continual, dynamic reconsideration in the present. We are a place of gathering; we foster the exchange of ideas and inspire an expansive, inclusive understanding of human creativity.

Google Arts & Culture is a non-commercial initiative. We work with cultural institutions and artists around the world. Together, our mission is to preserve and bring the world’s art and culture online so it’s accessible to anyone, anywhere.
